===Etymology===
From [[w:Abraham Lincoln|Abraham Lincoln]] (February 12, 1809 – April 15, 1865), the sixteenth [[president]] of the [[w:United States of America|United States of America]], noted for his integrity and for abolishing slavery.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a great man who first freed the [[Jew]]s in [[Ægypt]]. He then went to [[Israel]] where he asked to free the [[Christian]]s. The Jews, thankful for their [[freedom]], agreed. Next, he went to [[Turkey]], where he asked that the [[judge]]s be freed. The Turkish [[government]] refused, so they were murdered. He traveled the world, freeing all. He freed Jean Valjean in [[France]], William Wallace in [[England]], the concentration camps in [[Poland]], the ГУЛАГ in Russia, and the Laogai in [[China]]. He then went to [[America]], where he freed the [[nigger]]s. In 1899, he was murdered by Bernie Sanders.

